      <p class="abouttext">
        The Nordic Selection Event for DTBD is a selection held at NITH in Oslo, Norway, where teams from all over the Nordic region competes for a spot in Scotland. <br/><br/>


        This is the website for the Nordic selection event for the international games development competition Dare to be Digital. The best Nordic team get to go to Scotland for the summer and set their game idea into life!<br/><br/>

        Dare to be Digital (or Dare as it is commonly known) is the premier video games development competition for University students and recent graduates and the only route to a BAFTA Ones To Watch Award.<br/><br/>

        Teams of programming and arts students from Universities and Art Colleges across the globe gather at Abertay University in Dundee, Scotland for 9 weeks during the summer break to develop their own video game. They get mentoring from games industry staff who visit throughout the competition, free accommodation in Abertay University's Halls of Residence, and stipend while the competition lasts.<br/><br/>

        At the end of the competition in August the teams head to Edinburgh, Scotland to showcase their games at an event called Dare ProtoPlay, where the general public and games industry executives will play and vote for their games. The three winning teams will each become the sole nominess for a BAFTA Ones To Watch Award.
      </p>
